    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Hello.</p>

<p>Today is great to use a Vector datatype in Adobe Flex/Flash. It's like a strong-typed Array with better performance and other features (especially with thousands objects)</p>

<p>It would be perfect to have a Vector support in Zend_AMF.</p>

<p>Now, if you have in Flex VO with "public var users:Vector." and you send this VO to Zend_AMF, Zend_AMF server failed in deserialization with an exception "Unsupported type marker...".</p>

<p>Of course, it would be necessary to resolve how to have a Vector typed in PHP and how to resolve class-mapping (maybe some special datatype like a Zend_DataType_Vector?)</p>

<p>Thank you and good luck in the further development!</p>

